Title: PERFECT SIMULATION OF CONDITIONALLY SPECIFIED MODELS  
Keyword: Coupling from the past; exact simulation; Gibbs sampling; locally specified exponential family distributions; Markov chain Monte Carlo; Metropolis-Hastings algorithm; spatial statistics.  
Note: AMS 1991 MATHEMATICS SUBJECT CLASSIFICATION: 62H11, 62M30, 60K35.  
Address: Vej 7E, DK-9220 Aalborg Denmark.  
Affiliation: Jesper Mtller, Department of Mathematics, Aalborg University, Fredrik Bajers  
Date: May 7, 1998  
Abstract: We discuss how the ideas of producing perfect simulations based on coupling from the past for finite state space models naturally extend to mul-tivariate distributions with infinite or uncountable state spaces such as auto-gamma, auto-Poisson and auto-negative-binomial models, using Gibbs sampling in combination with sandwiching methods originally introduced for perfect simulation of point processes. 
